      "document": "[chunk 2]\nTitle: [2512.03324] Cache What Lasts: Token Retention for Memory-Bounded KV Cache in LLMs\nURL: https://arxiv.org/abs/2512.03324\nSection: \n\n-memory regimes. Remarkably, it even surpasses full-cache models in some settings, showing that selective retention can serve as a form of regularization, suppressing noise from uninformative tokens. Qualitative analyses further reveal that learned retention scores align with human intuition, naturally recovering heuristics such as sink tokens, sliding windows, and gist compression without explicit design. Beyond efficiency, retention scores provide insights into layer- and head-specific roles, suggesting a new path toward LLM interpretability.\n\nSubjects:\n\nMachine Learning (cs.LG)\n\n; Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI)\n\nCite as:\n\narXiv:2512.03324\n\n[cs.LG]\n\n(or\n\narXiv:2512.03324v2\n\n[cs.LG]\n\nfor this version)\n\nhttps://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2512.03324\n\nFocus to learn more\n\narXiv-issued DOI via DataCite\n\nSubmission history\n\nFrom: Ngoc Bui [\n\nview email\n\n[v1]\n\nWed, 3 Dec 2025 00:20:35 UTC (46,191 KB)\n\n[v2]\n\nSun, 1 Mar 2026 03:46:03 UTC (33,685 KB)\n\nFull-text links:\n\nAccess Paper:\n\nView a PDF of the paper titled Cache What Lasts: Token Retentio"
